{% extends '_base.html.jinja' %}

{% block more_head %}
<title>Hello World</title> 
<style>
main {
  color: #135;
}
</style>
{% endblock more_head %}

{% block body %}
<main>
<h1>Hello World!</h1>

{% filter markdown %}

The following is generated from markdown:

* one
* two
* three

The `this` variable is convenient:

<pre>
{{this|tojson}}
</pre>

Call functions from any module.

The `jinjagenadd` has convenient function to remove `index.html` from the end
of URLs like automatically changing "/index.html"
to "{{'/index.html' | index2dot}}".

And filters and functions for dates: {{today() | dateformat}}

{% endfilter %}

<pre>
{{'<hr>'|safe|escape}}
</pre>

Now let's include <strong>raw jinja code</strong>, but without it getting
interpreted as jinja template at all.  To be extra wild we'll raw include the
jinja template that generated this web page!
<hr>
<pre>
{{include_raw('index.html.jinja').unescape() | escape}}
</pre>
<hr>

</main>
{% endblock body %}
